        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 25 at 4:19PM MDT by NWS Denver CO</headline>
        <description>At 419 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Windsor, or 8 miles southeast of Fort Collins, moving east at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down small tree branches and blow
around unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Western Greeley, Windsor, Severance and New Windsor Reservoir.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Heavy rain is occurring with this storm and may lead to flooding. Do
not drive your vehicle through flooded roadways.</instruction>
